hey, hey.

06:00.525 --> 06:03.727
Pull the plug on that, huh?

06:03.795 --> 06:06.630
Well, how do you
like it, Archie?

06:06.698 --> 06:10.268
I thought we were saving
our green stamps for a camera.

06:12.104 --> 06:15.440
That's a beautiful fur there.
She looks fabulous.
Can't you say something nice?

06:15.507 --> 06:20.378
What's nice about it?
It probably took every
stamp book we had.

06:20.446 --> 06:24.082
No, Archie.
It's a present
from cousin Amelia...

06:24.149 --> 06:26.750
For looking after
her gall bladder.

06:28.354 --> 06:32.156
Oh, a present
from cousin Amelia, huh?
Mm-hmm.

06:32.224 --> 06:36.194
- Well, give it back.
- Oh, Archie. Why?

06:36.261 --> 06:38.196
Because a present
from cousin Amelia...

06:38.263 --> 06:41.265
Is also a present from
your cousin-in-law Russ too.

06:41.333 --> 06:44.068
And you ain't accepting
no gifts from Russel dekuyper.

06:44.136 --> 06:46.737
But daddy,
ma did something
nice for Amelia.

06:46.805 --> 06:50.541
Now Amelia's doing
something nice for ma.
Yeah, she earned that cape.

06:50.609 --> 06:53.011
Listen, Sonny boy.
In the first place,

06:53.078 --> 06:56.580
earning is a subject
you know nothing about.

06:59.351 --> 07:02.053
And in the second place,
that cape ain't earned.

07:02.121 --> 07:05.956
That's charity,
which Archie bunker don't take
from nobody in the third place.

07:06.025 --> 07:09.760
What charity, arch? It's a gift.
That isn't largesse.

07:09.828 --> 07:15.733
I ain't saying
it's largesse, "smallesse"
or any kind of "esse."

07:15.800 --> 07:18.936
When I want my wife
to have a fur coat,
I'll buy her a fur coat.

07:19.004 --> 07:21.639
You will?
No.

07:24.443 --> 07:27.845
Daddy, can't you understand
how ma feels about having
her very own mink?

07:27.913 --> 07:33.584
I can understand that she's
gonna give that fur cape back
to the dekuypers, that's all.

07:33.652 --> 07:35.953
Russ dekuyper.
He's rich.

07:36.021 --> 07:38.622
So he's always lauding it
over the whole world.

07:38.690 --> 07:42.126
He spends his life looking
for wounds to rub salt into.

07:42.194 --> 07:45.196
He sure found one with you.
You're practically green
with jealousy.

07:45.264 --> 07:48.399
What are you talking about?
Jealous of who, Russ dekuyper?

07:48.467 --> 07:51.102
Why, the man ain't
got of a gleaming feature.

07:51.170 --> 07:54.705
He ain't smart.
He ain't certainly
what you'd call good-looking.

07:54.773 --> 07:56.707
You mean like you?

07:58.810 --> 08:03.448
Well, now that you mention,
yeah. Ask Edith.
She knows the two of us.

08:03.515 --> 08:06.817
Who's better looking Edith, me
or that dumb dutchman dekuyper.

08:06.885 --> 08:10.988
You are, Archie, by far.
Satisfied?

08:11.056 --> 08:13.091
Can I keep the cape now?

08:13.158 --> 08:15.093
No.

08:16.895 --> 08:20.864
Now will you quit fooling around
and get chow on the table?
All right, Archie.

08:20.932 --> 08:23.667
Oh, boy.
"Oh, boy."
Yeah. Yeah.

08:23.735 --> 08:25.869
And what are you
looking at anyway?

08:25.937 --> 08:28.839
I'm surprised at youse two
"ecrology" nuts...

08:28.907 --> 08:31.442
Encouraging your mother
there to wear fur.

08:31.510 --> 08:36.581
They breed those animals, daddy.
That's right, arch. Mink is not
an endangered species.

08:36.648 --> 08:40.251
Oh, geez.
Them minks hangin' around your
mother-in-law's neck out there,

08:40.318 --> 08:44.020
they'll be glad to hear that--
that they ain't endangered,
just murdered.

08:44.089 --> 08:47.225
Besides, your mother-in-law
ain't a mink-type person.

08:47.292 --> 08:53.131
I mean, it's like puttin'
a white tie and tails
on the meathead here.

08:55.134 --> 08:57.168
Hold it, Edith.
Wait a minute.

08:57.236 --> 08:59.570
Is this all we're having?
Oh, no, Archie.

08:59.638 --> 09:03.441
We're having spaghetti just
the way you like it-- long.

09:03.509 --> 09:06.544
Oh. I like it short.

09:06.612 --> 09:09.247
I thought you liked it long...

09:09.314 --> 09:14.485
Except in the case of elbow
macaroni which is short
because it's bent.

09:17.822 --> 09:20.358
You're a pip,
you know that, Edith?

09:20.425 --> 09:22.360
A real pip.

09:22.427 --> 09:25.796
- Go on.
Get me the long spaghetti.
- Right away, Archie.

09:25.864 --> 09:28.932
Your mother's getting
dingbattier than ever
with that cape around her there.

09:29.000 --> 09:31.135
And that's why
that Russ dekuyper
sent it over here,

09:31.203 --> 09:33.337
to "percolate"
my family against me.

09:33.405 --> 09:35.339
To fill their minds
with the thought...

09:35.407 --> 09:37.841
That I ain't
rich enough to buy my wife
the thing she wants.

09:37.909 --> 09:41.812
- Well, daddy, you're not.
- You see that? It's poisoning
your mind already.

09:41.880 --> 09:44.248
I'm not gonna stand for this.
Edith, before you
sit down to eat,

09:44.316 --> 09:46.250
you get on the phone,
you call the dekuypers.

09:46.318 --> 09:48.252
You tell Amelia
you're giving back that cape.

09:48.320 --> 09:52.122
Oh, no, Archie.
I can't do that. I can't
hurt her feelings that way.

09:52.191 --> 09:54.659
Oh, well,
if you can't, I can.

09:54.726 --> 09:57.795
I'll make the phone call
myself, that's all.
Archie, please don't do that.

09:57.862 --> 10:01.265
Don't tell me what to do, Edith.
Just get the spaghetti
on the table.

10:01.333 --> 10:04.868
But Archie--
no, don't "but" me "but" me.
Just do what you're told.

10:04.936 --> 10:08.272
Archie, I'll give the cape back,
but don't insult them.

10:08.340 --> 10:11.576
Oh, no.
I'm gonna straighten out
Russ dekuyper right now.

10:11.643 --> 10:14.912
Daddy, they're
coming over here Friday.
Why can't you wait till then?

10:14.979 --> 10:18.549
Because I wanna throw
that cape back into his face
while I'm in the mood.

10:18.617 --> 10:21.352
Arch--
go on, Edith.

10:21.420 --> 10:23.354
Dummy up.

10:23.422 --> 10:25.823
Hello?
Hey, is that you, Russ?

10:25.890 --> 10:27.825
This is Archie bunker here.

10:27.892 --> 10:30.761
Yeah, uh, Russ,
about that fur cape
you sent over here.

10:30.829 --> 10:32.763
Well, Edith can't use it.

10:32.831 --> 10:35.533
No, no, no.
She can't take your fur, Russ.

10:35.601 --> 10:38.202
Cat fur, rabbit,
anything like that, you know.

10:38.270 --> 10:42.340
Yeah, she's got, uh--
what do you call these--
allergies.

10:42.407 --> 10:46.009
Yeah. Oh, geez.
She's sneezing her
face off right now.

10:46.077 --> 10:49.012
Gesundheit in there, Edith.

10:49.080 --> 10:51.014
I just wanna say,
when you come over
Friday night...

10:51.082 --> 10:55.419
You pick up the fur and you
give it away to the "salivation"
army or something like that.

10:55.487 --> 10:57.821
Russ, I can't talk now
because they're serving dinner.

10:57.889 --> 11:00.558
I gotta go.
That's all. Good-bye.

11:00.626 --> 11:02.560
Well, it's final now, Edith!

11:02.628 --> 11:05.095
You're gonna
give back that cape!
